relevant_findings: Vesicles on an erythematous base in the right external auditory canal, right mandible, and under the right lip.
Decreased sensation to light touch with paresthesia and dysesthesia over right V2 and V3.
Single vesicular lesion inside the right side of her mouth.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: The vesicular lesions erupted and became scabby. By the second visit, the swelling had decreased and a dull feeling was reported in the back of the head and face.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Continued reporting of right facial pain, especially with chewing. Physical examination showed no new abnormalities.
